<TITLE> Indian court okays Lafarge Surma quarrying in Meghalaya </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 DHAKA, Nov 26 (bdnews24.com) -- India's Supreme Court has issued a ruling allowing a Bangladeshi cement company to quarry lime stones from the Indian state of Meghalaya, the foreign ministry said in a statement Monday. The ruling was facilitated by the withdrawal of objections by the related authorities in India, the statement said. Bangladesh had been requesting India to take measures to allow the uninterrupted operations of Lafarge Surma Cement, whose plant in Chhattak in the district of Sylhet depends on limestone from Meghalaya. "I see the withdrawal of objections by the concerned Indian Ministry as a positive gesture in line with our growing bilateral relations," foreign affairs adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury was quoted as saying. bdn
